| 1869 || || Legislation || Department of Agriculture|| The {{w|Immigration Act, 1869}} is passed. The Act allows largely free migration, and is made as such to encourage settlement of the Western provinces (as opposed to using Canada as a transit stop on the way to the United States). It includes provisions regulating the conditions of travel on ships arriving in Canada. Immigration is now under the Department of Agriculture<ref name=pier21-immigration-act-1869>{{cite web|url = https://www.pier21.ca/research/immigration-history/immigration-act-1869|title = Immigration Act, 1869|accessdate = November 24, 2017|publisher = Canada Museum of Immigration at Pier21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://immigrationtous.net/139-immigration-act-canada-1869.html|title = IMMIGRATION ACT (CANADA) (1869)|accessdate = November 24, 2017|publisher = Immigration to North America}}</ref><ref name=passagetocanada/><ref name=pier21/>
